            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@untitaker - IIRC modification of the environment after initialization is supposed to be a bad idea, see: http://jinja.pocoo.org/docs/api/#jinja2.Environment .\n\n@jncornett - The other pattern is supposed to be overriding \"create_jinja_environment\", see:\n\n``` python\n 652     def create_jinja_environment(self):\n 653         \"\"\"Creates the Jinja2 environment based on :attr:`jinja_options`\n 654         and :meth:`select_jinja_autoescape`.  Since 0.7 this also adds\n 655         the Jinja2 globals and filters after initialization.  Override\n 656         this function to customize the behavior.\n 657\n 658         .. versionadded:: 0.5\n 659         .. versionchanged:: 1.0\n 660            ``Environment.auto_reload`` set in accordance with\n 661            ``TEMPLATES_AUTO_RELOAD`` configuration option.\n 662\n 663         \"\"\"\n```\n\nSo I might do something like this instead of the patch I submitted, which is clunkier and relies on the ImmutableDict jinja_options as effectively being part of the API:\n\n```\nMyFlask(Flask):\n  def create_jinja_environment(self):\n    self.jinja_options = ImmutableDict( undefined=StrictUndefined, etc )\n    return super(Flask, self).create_jinja_environment()\n```\n"
        },
